**Important Notes:**

- **When translations are requested**, use `useTranslations` when filter options use enum values (same pattern as column definitions). **By default, use hard-coded English labels.**
- When using translations, use `useMemo` to memoize filter options with translation function in dependency array
- Translation keys should follow the pattern: `enums.{enum_name}` (e.g., `enums.route_type`, `enums.trip_status`)
- Enum values are used as string keys in translation files (e.g., `"1": "Fixed Route"`)
- Wrap filter options in `useMemo` to prevent unnecessary re-renders when translations change
- Ensure translation functions are called before any early returns (hooks must be called unconditionally)

## Row Actions Pattern

**⚠️ CRITICAL: ALL row actions (view, edit, delete, etc.) MUST use `setRowAction` with appropriate variants. DO NOT use separate `onEdit` or `onView` callbacks.**

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Actions should NOT be visible if the user doesn't have permission. Always check permissions before adding actions to `availableActions` and use the `hidden` property as a secondary guard.**

**✅ PREFERRED: Include `hidden` directly in the `createRowActions` object**

The `hidden` property should be included directly in each action object passed to `createRowActions`. This is cleaner and more maintainable than using `.map()` to add `hidden` after creating actions.

**✅ CORRECT: All actions use `setRowAction` and are always defined**

```typescript
// ✅ DO: Always define actions, use hidden property with !!!permissions?.action pattern
const actions = createRowActions({
  view: {
    hidden: () => !!!permissions?.view,
    onClick: () => setRowAction({ row, variant: 'view' })
  },
  edit: {
    hidden: () => !!!permissions?.edit,
    onClick: () => setRowAction({ row, variant: 'update' })
  },
  delete: {
    hidden: () => !!!permissions?.delete,
    onClick: () => setRowAction({ row, variant: 'delete' })
  }
})
```

**❌ WRONG: Conditional action creation**

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: Conditionally create actions with ternary operators
const actions = createRowActions({
  delete: permissions.delete
    ? {
        hidden: () => !permissions.delete,
        onClick: () => setRowAction({ row, variant: 'delete' })
      }
    : undefined,
  edit: permissions.edit
    ? {
        hidden: () => !permissions.edit,
        onClick: () => setRowAction({ row, variant: 'update' })
      }
    : undefined
})
```

**❌ WRONG: Using separate callbacks for edit/view**

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: Use separate onEdit/onView callbacks
type UseColumnsProps = {
  onEdit?: (id: number) => void // ❌ WRONG
  onView?: (id: number) => void // ❌ WRONG
  setRowAction: (action?: DataTableRowAction<T> | null) => void
}

// ❌ DON'T: Call separate callbacks in actions
const actions = createRowActions({
  view: {
    onClick: () => onView?.(row.original.id) // ❌ WRONG
  },
  edit: {
    onClick: () => onEdit?.(row.original.id) // ❌ WRONG
  }
})
```

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: Use .map() to add hidden after createRowActions
const actions = createRowActions({
  view: () => setRowAction({ row, variant: 'view' }),
  edit: () => setRowAction({ row, variant: 'update' })
}).map((action) => {
  if (action.id === 'view') {
    return { ...action, hidden: () => !permissions.view }
  }
  return action
})
```

### Row Action Variants

Supported variants:

- `view` - View details
- `edit` - Edit item
- `delete` - Delete item
- `accept` - Accept request
- `reject` - Reject request

### Row Action Handler

**⚠️ CRITICAL: ALWAYS use `useRowActions` hook for row action handling. The hook provides `setRowAction`, `deleteDialog`, and `permissions` automatically.**

**✅ CORRECT: Use useRowActions hook**

```typescript
// Constants moved outside component to avoid recreation
const PERMISSIONS_CONFIG = {
  delete: PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_DESTROY,
  update: PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_UPDATE,
  view: PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_SHOW
} as const

// ✅ DO: Use useRowActions hook for all row actions
const { deleteDialog, permissions, setRowAction } = useRowActions<Feature>({
  deleteDialogConfig: {
    description: 'Are you sure you want to delete this feature?',
    getItemName: (feature) => feature.name,
    title: 'Delete Feature'
  },
  deleteMutationOptions: deleteFeatureMutationOptions,
  permissions: PERMISSIONS_CONFIG,
  redirectOnUpdate: (feature) => `/features/${feature.id}/edit`,
  redirectOnView: (feature) => `/features/${feature.id}`
})

// ✅ DO: Pass setRowAction and permissions from hook to columns
const columns = useFeatureColumns({
  permissions,
  setRowAction
})
```

**❌ WRONG: Manual setRowAction callback**

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: Manual setRowAction callback when useRowActions can be used
const router = useRouter()
const { hasPermission } = usePermissions()
const [deleteItem, setDeleteItem] = useState<Feature | null>(null)
const [deleteOpen, setDeleteOpen] = useState(false)

const setRowAction = useCallback(
  (rowAction?: DataTableRowAction<Feature> | null) => {
    if (!rowAction) return
    const { row, variant } = rowAction
    const item = row.original
    switch (variant) {
      case 'delete':
        setDeleteItem(item)
        setDeleteOpen(true)
        break
      case 'update':
        router.push(`/features/${item.id}/edit`)
        break
      // ... other cases
    }
  },
  [router]
)

// ❌ DON'T: Manual permission checking
const columns = useFeatureColumns({
  permissions: {
    delete: hasPermission(PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_DESTROY),
    edit: hasPermission(PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_UPDATE),
    view: hasPermission(PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_SHOW)
  },
  setRowAction
})
```

**❌ WRONG: Separate callbacks for edit/view**

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: Create separate handleEdit/handleView callbacks
const handleEdit = useCallback(
  (id: number) => {
    router.push(`/features/${id}`)
  },
  [router]
)

const handleView = useCallback(
  (id: number) => {
    router.push(`/features/${id}`)
  },
  [router]
)

// ❌ DON'T: Pass onEdit/onView to columns
const columns = useFeatureColumns({
  onEdit: handleEdit,  // ❌ WRONG - should use setRowAction
  onView: handleView,  // ❌ WRONG - should use setRowAction
  permissions: { ... },
  setRowAction
})
```

### Delete Confirmation Dialog Pattern

**⚠️ CRITICAL: ALWAYS use `useRowActions` hook for delete dialog management. The hook handles delete state, dialog rendering, and permissions internally.**

**⚠️ CRITICAL: Delete dialog is automatically rendered by `useRowActions` hook and passed as prop to `DataTable` component. DO NOT manually render `DeleteConfirmationDialog`.**

**✅ CORRECT: Use useRowActions hook pattern**

**Step 1: Export mutationOptions from query layer**

```typescript
// query/{feature}/{feature}-mutations.ts
import { mutationOptions } from '@tanstack/react-query'
import { AxiosError } from 'axios'
import { fetcher } from '@/lib/fetcher'
import { ENDPOINTS } from '@/query-client'

export const delete{Feature}MutationOptions = mutationOptions<
  API,
  AxiosError<API>,
  number | string
>({
  meta: {
    invalidatesQuery: [['{feature}']]
  },
  mutationFn: async (id) =>
    fetcher(ENDPOINTS.{FEATURE}.DELETE(id), {
      auth: true,
      method: 'DELETE'
    })
})
```

**Step 2: Use useRowActions hook in table component**

**✅ CORRECT: Use useRowActions hook with deleteDialogConfig and deleteMutationOptions**

```typescript
'use client'

import React from 'react'
// When translations are requested, add: import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl'

import { DataTable, DataTableToolbar } from '@/components/data-table'
import { useDataTable } from '@/hooks/use-data-table'
import { useRowActions } from '@/hooks/use-row-actions'
import { cn } from '@/utils'

import { useFeatureColumns } from '@/app/(app)/{feature}/_{feature}/columns/{feature}-columns'
import { PERMISSIONS } from '@/lib/auth/permissions'
import { getAllFeatureQuery, Feature, deleteFeatureMutationOptions } from '@/query/{feature}'

// Constants moved outside component to avoid recreation
const PERMISSIONS_CONFIG = {
  delete: PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_DESTROY,
  update: PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_UPDATE,
  view: PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_SHOW
} as const

export const FeatureTable: React.FC<{ className?: string }> = ({
  className
}) => {
  // When translations are requested, add:
  // const tDeleteDialog = useTranslations('{feature}.deleteDialog')

  const { deleteDialog, permissions, setRowAction } = useRowActions<Feature>({
    deleteDialogConfig: {
      description: 'Are you sure you want to delete this feature?',
      getItemName: (feature) => feature.name,
      title: 'Delete Feature'
    },
    deleteMutationOptions: deleteFeatureMutationOptions,
    permissions: PERMISSIONS_CONFIG,
    redirectOnUpdate: (feature) => `/features/${feature.id}/edit`,
    redirectOnView: (feature) => `/features/${feature.id}`
  })

  const columns = useFeatureColumns({
    permissions,
    setRowAction
  })

  // ... table setup code ...

  return (
    <main className={cn('relative m-5', className)}>
      <DataTable
        deleteDialog={deleteDialog}
        error={error}
        isError={isError}
        isLoading={isLoading}
        refetch={refetch}
        table={table}
        toolbar={...}
      />
      {/* When translations are requested, replace hard-coded strings in deleteDialogConfig:
          deleteDialogConfig: {
            description: tDeleteDialog('description'),
            title: tDeleteDialog('title')
          }
      */}
    </main>
  )
}
```

**❌ WRONG: Wrapping deleteDialogConfig in useMemo**

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: useMemo is unnecessary - useRowActions hook handles memoization internally
const DELETE_DIALOG_CONFIG = {
  description: 'Are you sure you want to delete this feature?',
  title: 'Delete Feature'
} as const

export const FeatureTable: React.FC<{ className?: string }> = ({
  className
}) => {
  // ❌ WRONG: useMemo wrapper is unnecessary
  const deleteDialogConfig = useMemo(
    () => ({
      ...DELETE_DIALOG_CONFIG,
      getItemName: (feature: Feature) => feature.name
    }),
    []
  )

  const { deleteDialog, permissions, setRowAction } = useRowActions<Feature>({
    deleteDialogConfig, // ❌ WRONG: Pass object directly instead
    deleteMutationOptions: deleteFeatureMutationOptions,
    permissions: PERMISSIONS_CONFIG
  })
}
```

**Why this is wrong:**

- The `useRowActions` hook already handles memoization internally using `useCallback` for `getItemName` and `useMemo` for `deleteDialog`
- Wrapping `deleteDialogConfig` in `useMemo` creates unnecessary object recreation
- The hook's internal memoization is sufficient and optimized
- For translation cases, `tDeleteDialog` is stable, so no memoization needed

**❌ WRONG: Manual delete state management and dialog rendering**

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: Manual useState for delete state
const [deleteItem, setDeleteItem] = useState<Feature | null>(null)
const [deleteOpen, setDeleteOpen] = useState(false)

// ❌ DON'T: Manual setRowAction callback
const setRowAction = useCallback(
  (rowAction?: DataTableRowAction<Feature> | null) => {
    if (rowAction?.variant === 'delete') {
      setDeleteItem(rowAction.row.original)
      setDeleteOpen(true)
    }
  },
  []
)

// ❌ DON'T: Manual DeleteConfirmationDialog rendering
{deleteItem && (
  <DeleteConfirmationDialog
    isOpen={deleteOpen}
    mutationFnParam={deleteItem.id}
    mutationOptions={deleteFeatureMutationOptions}
    onClose={() => setDeleteItem(null)}
    onOpenChange={setDeleteOpen}
    title="Delete Feature"
  />
)}
```

**❌ WRONG: Manual permission checking in table components**

```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: Manual usePermissions hook and inline permission checks
const { hasPermission } = usePermissions()

const columns = useFeatureColumns({
  permissions: {
    delete: hasPermission(PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_DESTROY),
    edit: hasPermission(PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_UPDATE),
    view: hasPermission(PERMISSIONS.FEATURES_SHOW)
  },
  setRowAction
})
```

**Key Points:**

- ✅ **ALWAYS use `useRowActions` hook** - Handles delete state, dialog rendering, and permissions internally
- ✅ **Pass `deleteDialog` to `DataTable`** - Dialog is rendered automatically by the hook
- ✅ **Use returned `permissions`** - Permissions are computed internally from permission keys
- ✅ **Configure via props** - Pass `deleteMutationOptions`, `deleteDialogConfig`, and `permissions` to hook
- ✅ **No manual state management** - Hook handles `deleteItem` and `deleteOpen` internally
- ✅ **No manual permission checking** - Hook uses `usePermissions` internally
- ❌ **DO NOT manually manage delete state** - Use `useRowActions` hook instead
- ❌ **DO NOT manually render DeleteConfirmationDialog** - Pass `deleteDialog` prop to `DataTable`
- ❌ **DO NOT use `usePermissions` in table components** - Permissions come from `useRowActions` return value
- ❌ **DO NOT create custom delete dialog components** - Use `useRowActions` hook pattern

