### Date Columns

**⚠️⚠️⚠️ MANDATORY: ALL date/time columns MUST use `Column.DateColumn` ⚠️⚠️⚠️**

**This is a non-negotiable requirement. ALL date/time values displayed in table columns MUST use `Column.DateColumn` from `@/components/data-table/columns/date`. No exceptions.**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Use Column.DateColumn for all date/time columns
{
  accessorKey: 'created_at',
  cell: ({ row }) => (
    <Column.DateColumn value={row.original.created_at} />
  ),
  enableHiding: true,
  header: ({ column }) => (
    <DataTableColumnHeader column={column} title="Created" />
  ),
  id: 'created_at'
}

// ✅ CORRECT: Updated date column
{
  accessorKey: 'updated_at',
  cell: ({ row }) => (
    <Column.DateColumn value={row.original.updated_at} />
  ),
  enableHiding: true,
  header: ({ column }) => (
    <DataTableColumnHeader column={column} title="Updated" />
  ),
  id: 'updated_at'
}

// ❌ WRONG: Manual date formatting - STRICTLY FORBIDDEN
cell: ({ row }) => {
  const date = new Date(row.original.created_at)
  return <Column.Text text={date.toLocaleDateString()} />
}

// ❌ WRONG: Using formatDate directly in cell - STRICTLY FORBIDDEN
// Use Column.DateColumn instead - it uses formatDate internally
cell: ({ row }) => {
  const { date } = formatDate(row.original.created_at)
  return <Column.Text text={date} />
}

// ❌ WRONG: Any other date formatting method - STRICTLY FORBIDDEN
cell: ({ row }) => {
  return <span>{new Intl.DateTimeFormat().format(new Date(row.original.created_at))}</span>
}
```

**Why this is mandatory:**

- **Consistency**: Ensures all dates are formatted identically across the application
- **Locale support**: Automatic Arabic/English locale detection and formatting
- **Timezone handling**: Proper client timezone conversion
- **RTL support**: Correct right-to-left layout for Arabic
- **Maintainability**: Single source of truth for date formatting logic
- **User experience**: Smart formatting (Today/Yesterday) improves readability

## Important Note:

Don't add any new permissions in permissions file. If the feature doesn't include a key, add a concise `//@TODO` comment: `//@TODO: Add {resource}.{action} permission`

## Integration Checklist

When creating a new table, ensure:

- [ ] File structure follows pattern
- [ ] Query options defined in query folder
- [ ] Mutations defined for all actions
- [ ] Types defined for all data models
- [ ] Columns file created with proper structure
- [ ] Params hook created for URL state
- [ ] Permissions defined in permissions.ts
- [ ] Permissions checked in columns and buttons
- [ ] Row actions handler implemented
- [ ] Table configured with useDataTable
- [ ] Page structure follows template
- [ ] Endpoints defined in ENDPOINTS
- [ ] Loading and error states handled (pass `isLoading`, `isError`, `error`, `refetch` props to `DataTable` - **DO NOT use `errorDescription` or `errorTitle`**)
- [ ] Responsive design implemented
- [ ] Accessibility requirements met
